Share this on WhatsAppFollowing an exclusive report detailing the failing health of Bola Tinubu hospitalized abroad, the APC national leader landed at the Muritala Mohammed Airport, the international wing, June 15.
The online platform had reported how he collapsed, and had to be winged out of France for better medical attention, and how all that related to his 2023 presidential ambition.
“Tinubu is in Paris, France for a medical checkup. His health is deteriorating due to old age,” the news platform quoted a top source as saying, a couple of hours before Tinubu arrived Nigeria.
Tunde Rahaman, Tinubu’s media aide, said his boss just came back from a trip abroad.
The APC leader was accompanied by his aides when he disembarked at the airport.
